        <p>Before touching the patient, ensure you follow the core protocol:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>W</strong>ash Hands.</li>
            <li><strong>I</strong>ntroduce yourself.</li>
            <li><strong>P</strong>ermission (Consent).</li>
            <li><strong>E</strong>xposure (Chest exposed, 45¬∞ angle).</li>
            <li><strong>R</strong>eposition (Patient comfort).</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="info-box" style="border-color: var(--text-muted);">
            üí° <strong>Essential:</strong> Always approach the patient from the right side.
