    <div id="step-2" class="card">
        <h2>üëÄ Inspection</h2>
        <p>Look from the end of the bed, then look closer.</p>
        
        <h3>General Inspection</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Hands:</strong> Clubbing, Splinter Haemorrhages, Tar staining.</li>
            <li><strong>Face:</strong> Malar Flush (Mitral Stenosis), Pallor (Anaemia).</li>
            <li><strong>Neck:</strong> JVP height (Indicates right heart pressure).</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Precordium (Chest)</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Scars:</strong> Midline Sternotomy (CABG/Valve), Pacemaker scar.</li>
            <li><strong>Heaves:</strong> Visible pulsations.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="audio-player">
            <span>üîä <strong>Audio Note:</strong> Inspecting Scars</span>
