        <h2>‚úã Palpation</h2>
        
        <h3>1. Apex Beat</h3>
        <p>Locate the <strong>Apex Beat</strong> (5th ICS, Mid-clavicular line).</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Displaced? (LV Dilation)</li>
            <li>Tapping? (Mitral Stenosis)</li>
            <li>Heaving? (LV Hypertrophy)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Parasternal Heave</h3>
        <p>Place heel of hand on left sternal edge. Lift indicates RV Hypertrophy.</p>

        <h3>3. Thrills</h3>
        <p>Palpable murmurs over valve areas. Feels like a purring cat.</p>
    </div>

